# .clinerules — Cline Session Rules
# Workspace: c:\evm

## Session Start

At the start of every session, read the following files in order:
1. `CLAUDE.md` — root workspace orientation (project overview, EVM rules, key differences)
2. `evm-sv/CLAUDE.md` — deep EVM reference (all classes, methods, tasks, coding patterns)
3. `CLAUDE_UVM.md` — deep UVM reference (UVM architecture, all major classes, macros)

Do not skip these files. All three are required context for all work in this workspace.

---

## Documentation Update Rule

**Any change made to the evm-sv project MUST be reflected in `evm-sv/CLAUDE.md`.**

This includes but is not limited to:
- New classes, tasks, functions, or methods added to any `.sv` file
- Changes to existing API signatures or behavior
- New coding patterns or conventions introduced
- New protocol agents or vkit components added
- Changes to the register model, TLM, or sequencer infrastructure
- Any new macros or plusarg options

`evm-sv/CLAUDE.md` is the authoritative reference for the EVM framework. It must stay in sync with the actual source code at all times.

---

## File Header API Summary Rule

**Every `.sv` file in `evm-sv/` MUST include an `API:` section in its file header block.**

This section lists all public functions, tasks, and classes defined in that file — one line each with a brief description. Update this section whenever functions or tasks are added or changed.

Format:
```
// API — Public Interface:
//   ClassName.method_name(args)  — brief description
//   static_fn(args)              — brief description
```

Rules:
- Apply to any `.sv` file you create or modify in `evm-sv/`
- You do NOT need to retroactively update all files at once — update each file as it is next touched
- The two files most recently modified (`evm_report_handler.sv`, `evm_log.sv`) must be updated in the current session
- Mark P0.3 additions with `[P0.3]`, future additions with their tag (e.g., `[P0.1]`, `[P1.1]`)
